  "instructions": [
    "preheat oven to 400°f (200°c).",
    "in a medium saucepan, combine coconut rice, 1 cup water, and 1 tsp coconut oil. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes.",
    "in a large skillet, heat 2 tbsp canola oil over medium-high heat.",
    "add diced onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "add minced garlic and chopped scotch bonnet pepper; cook for 1 minute.",
    "add allspice, thyme, salt, and black pepper; cook for 1 minute.",
    "stir in shredded cabbage and cook until wilted, about 3 minutes.",
    "in a separate pan, cook diced bacon over medium heat until crispy.",
    "to assemble bao, place a portion of coconut rice mixture on each bun, followed by a spoonful of cabbage mixture, and top with crispy bacon and chopped cilantro.",
    "serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
